# Consumer App Visual Standards

When verifying, testing, or fixing app appearance, use this as the authoritative reference.

## Shared Visual Elements (All Consumer Apps)

Every DedgeAuth-integrated consumer app must have:

- **FK Green header/branding**: `#008942` gradient from tenant CSS
- **Dedge logo**: Loaded from DedgeAuth tenant logo endpoint (not local files)
- **DedgeAuth user menu**: `<div id="DedgeAuthUserMenu"></div>` -- top-right dropdown with user info, app switcher, logout
- **Tenant CSS injection**: `<style id="DedgeAuth-tenant-css">` populated dynamically by `DedgeAuth-user.js`

### CSS Load Order

1. App's own local CSS (`css/site.css` or similar)
2. DedgeAuth common CSS (`api/DedgeAuth/ui/common.css` via proxy)
3. Tenant-specific CSS (injected into `#DedgeAuth-tenant-css` by `user.js`)
4. DedgeAuth user menu CSS (`api/DedgeAuth/ui/user.css` via proxy)

### HTML Template (standard head/body pattern)

```html
<head>
  <!-- App's own CSS first -->
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="css/site.css">
  <!-- DedgeAuth common CSS via proxy -->
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="api/DedgeAuth/ui/common.css">
  <!-- Tenant CSS injected here by user.js -->
  <style id="DedgeAuth-tenant-css"></style>
  <!-- DedgeAuth user menu CSS -->
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="api/DedgeAuth/ui/user.css">
</head>
<body>
  <header>
    <!-- App branding + navigation -->
    <div id="DedgeAuthUserMenu"></div>
  </header>

  <main>
    <!-- App content -->
  </main>

  <!-- DedgeAuth user script (loads last) -->
  <script src="api/DedgeAuth/ui/user.js"></script>
</body>
```

## Visual Verification Checklist

- [ ] FK Green (`#008942`) header gradient visible
- [ ] Dedge logo loaded (not broken image)
- [ ] DedgeAuth user menu rendered in top-right
- [ ] App switcher dropdown lists all consumer apps
- [ ] Tenant CSS applied (header gradient, not plain white)
- [ ] Navigation links present and styled
- [ ] Content area rendered (not blank or unstyled)
- [ ] No console errors related to CSS/JS loading
- [ ] Page works under IIS virtual path (not just localhost root)

## Common Visual Issues

| Symptom | Cause | Fix |
|---------|-------|-----|
| Completely unstyled page | CSS paths use leading `/` (breaks under virtual app) | Use relative paths (no leading `/`) |
| Missing user menu | `user.js` not loaded or `DedgeAuthUserMenu` div missing | Add both to HTML |
| Broken logo | Hardcoded server URL instead of proxy | Use `api/DedgeAuth/ui/...` proxy path |
| No tenant branding | Missing `<style id="DedgeAuth-tenant-css">` tag | Add empty style tag for `user.js` to populate |
| CSS works locally but not on IIS | `MapFallbackToFile` intercepting trailing-slash redirect | Remove SPA fallback (see `no-spa-fallback.mdc`) |
